flowchart TD
    accTitle: AI to accessibility champion concept map
    accDescr {
        A concept map for Module 1. A single technical spine runs from
        Artificial Intelligence to Machine Learning to Deep Learning to
        Neural Networks to Large Language Models to Foundation Models to
        Generative AI, with each step representing a narrower subset or
        application. Generative AI produces accessibility drafts and
        explanations, which always pass through Human Review. Human Review
        branches into Accuracy, Privacy, Bias and Fairness, and Accessibility
        Expertise. GLOW workflows feed into Human Review and reach Campus
        Partners, who become Accessibility Champions. The center of the map
        is human-centered accessibility capacity building, not the AI model.
    }
    AI["Artificial Intelligence\n(the broad field)"]
    ML["Machine Learning\n(learns from data)"]
    DL["Deep Learning\n(multi-layer networks)"]
    NN["Neural Networks\n(e.g. transformers)"]
    LLM["Large Language Models\n(e.g. Claude, GPT-4o)"]
    FM["Foundation Models\n(broad pre-training)"]
    GenAI["Generative AI\n(e.g. Claude.ai, ChatGPT)"]
    Drafts["Accessibility Drafts\nand Explanations"]
    HumanReview["Human Review\n(required checkpoint)"]
    Accuracy["Accuracy"]
    Privacy["Privacy"]
    Bias["Bias and Fairness"]
    Access["Accessibility Expertise"]
    GLOW["GLOW Workflows\n(structured, teachable)"]
    Partners["Campus Partners"]
    Champions["Accessibility Champions"]

    AI -->|includes| ML
    ML -->|uses| DL
    DL -->|uses| NN
    NN -->|underlies| LLM
    LLM -->|is trained as| FM
    FM -->|enables| GenAI
    GenAI -->|produces| Drafts
    Drafts -->|require| HumanReview
    HumanReview -->|checks| Accuracy
    HumanReview -->|checks| Privacy
    HumanReview -->|checks| Bias
    HumanReview -->|applies| Access
    GLOW -->|structures| HumanReview
    GLOW -->|trains| Partners
    Partners -->|become| Champions
